        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 16 at 6:00PM CDT until May 16 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Salem in Fulton
County, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Heart...                          Mammoth Spring...
Fryatt...                         Flint Springs...
Saddler Falls...                  Wheeling...
Wirth...                          Saddle...
Salem in Fulton County...         Mammoth Spring State Park...
Salem Airport...                  Elm Store...
Camp...                           Glencoe...
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for eastern and
north central Arkansas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
